00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:42,480
you can't claim that you're
not calling those people terrorists

239
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:46,400
when your lower third says,
"Terrorists inbound ?".

240
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:49,000
If you're really not saying
they're terrorists,

241
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:51,080
change that
to something more accurate,

242
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,040
like "people take train".

243
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:56,200
Or "some wear hats,
others less so".

244
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:59,720
And second,
describing that as a new video

245
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:03,160
that sheds light on the migrant crisis
is a little misleading,

246
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:07,240
because in researching this story,
we found a version of that same video

247
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:10,480
uploaded onto YouTube
back in 2010,

248
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:13,520
well before this migrant crisis
even began.

249
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:16,400
And if you are going to use
misleading old footage

250
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:19,600
to try and make people frightened
of Muslims, why stop there ?

251
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:22,560
Just go the whole way and use
a clip from "True Lies".

252
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:25,800
We're not saying that
any of those people are terrorists

253
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:28,520
or are in any way affiliated
with a terror group,

254
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:31,320
but it does highlight just how
many of these refugees

255
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:34,360
who are fleeing violence
in Iraq and Syria are Muslim.

256
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:39,600
That's only about 10% more racist
than what you did.

257
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,200
So, let's just
take a step back,

258
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:46,400
because these people are coming
from many different countries

259
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:49,760
and fleeing everything from civil war
to economic stagnation.

260
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:53,480
And while each story is unique,
many of them are heartbreaking.

261
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:56,560
Noujain is 16
and from Kobani in Syria.

262
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:59,080
Disabled from birth,
she cannot walk.

263
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:01,760
She made the dangerous crossing
from Turkey last week.

264
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:05,880
I've been trying many things
for the first time during this journey,

265
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:08,040
like a train and a ship.

266
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:11,280
I just enjoyed it.

267
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,800
- You enjoyed it ?
- Yeah.

268
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:16,000
You're the first person
I've met who said that.

269
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:19,240
To understand why, you must know
the world she escaped from.

270
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:22,400
Imagine you're 16
and you're always afraid

271
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:24,320
to be dead at any minute.

272
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:26,200
What is your dream ?

273
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:31,560
I dream to be an astronaut
and find an alien.

274
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,800
Yes.

275
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,880
I want to meet the queen.

276
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:42,520
I think that girl absolutely deserves
to meet an alien and the queen,

277
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:46,120
and also, if she has time,
a real human with feelings.

278
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:51,120
But unfortunately for Noujain
and so many like her,

279
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:53,840
Europe has yet to create
an effective system

280
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:55,880
to process this influx of people.

281
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:58,400
Every country has a different
application process

282
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:01,320
and some are totally overwhelmed
and underfunded.

283
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:04,800
We actually got our hands
on a couple of registration forms

284
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,960
that were given to refugees
upon arrival.

285
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:09,520
This one was handed
to a Syrian asylum seeker

286
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,680
arriving in Greece
on September the 5th.

287
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:14,040
It tells him to return
for registration

288
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:16,400
on December the 21st,

289
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:18,640
and that could be
a tricky three-month wait,

290
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:21,320
because he's not allowed
to work in that time.

291
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:23,560
And yet, that is nothing
compared to this form

292
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,680
given to an Iraqi refugee
in Turkey

293
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:30,200
telling him to come back
on June 15th of 2017,

294
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:32,720
which sounds bad
before you notice

295
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:35,080
the pink sticky note
added at the bottom

296
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:39,480
clarifying that his actual date will be
February 19th, 2020 !

297
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,520
And that is ridiculous.

298
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:44,520
These people can't go
five years without working.

299
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:47,280
They're refugees,
not RenÃ©e Zellweger.

300
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:50,600
And facing that kind of limbo,

301
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:55,000
it's no wonder refugees want to try
to push deeper into Europe,

302
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:58,120
and many of them are heading
for one surprising country

303
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:00,280
that seems to actually want them.

304
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:04,600
They keep coming, thousands every day,
at the main train station in Munich,

305
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:08,600
often greeted by applauding locals
or welcoming volunteers.

306
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:12,280
It's no wonder that Germany
is the preferred destination

307
00:17:12,360 --> 00:17:14,320
for so many refugees.

308
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:16,960
Amazingly,
one of the warmest welcomes

309
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:19,720
on offer to immigrants
comes from Germany,

310
00:17:20,120 --> 00:17:22,320
a country whose idea
of a bedtime story

311
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:25,160
is two children being left
to die in the forest

312
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:28,880
before being nearly cooked and eaten,
and then murdering an old woman.

313
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,680
Sleep well.

314
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:35,240
Unfortunately, many politicians
in other countries than Germany

315
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:37,320
have been actively hostile

316
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:40,560
to anyone even considering
settling within their borders.

317
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:44,160
No way. You will not make
the Netherlands home.

318
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:49,640
Please don't come. We can't guarantee
that you will be accepted here.

319
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:52,720
The Danish government
has published these ads

320
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,920
in a number
of Lebanese newspapers.

321
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,480
The text is obviously
written in Arabic,

322
00:17:57,680 --> 00:18:00,320
and it's telling migrants,
"don't come to Denmark",

323
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:04,080
highlighting the tough regulations
and constraints that await them there.

324
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:08,400
Denmark is so adverse to taking
people in, it's basically placing

325
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:11,800
intentionally-missed-connections ads
in other countries.

326
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:13,720
"Me, Danish government official,"

327
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:16,080
"you, person in a Lebanese
refugee camp."

328
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:19,920
"From the moment I saw you,
I knew there was nothing between us."

329
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,320
Perfect. Send.

330
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:24,960
But even Denmark's
approach seems friendly

331
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:29,480
next to the video apparently produced
by the mayor of Asotthalom, Hungary,

332
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:32,960
showing exactly how he
and his police forces would prevent

333
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:35,160
migrants from coming to his town.

334
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:37,680
Hungary is a bad choice.

335
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:40,600
Asotthalom is the worst.

336
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:09,240
Okay, a few things there.

337
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:12,080
First, you can add as much
scary music as you want.

338
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:15,360
There is nothing imposing
about one van driving alone

339
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:17,080
on a country road.

340
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:19,320
The only message that
your sending is

341
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:22,440
"make sure you wait
for that one van to pass by".

342
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:25,040
And second of all, Mr. Mayor,
you do realize

343
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:29,160
that border police and nightclub
bouncers are not the same thing ?

344
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:34,440
Refugees aren't welcome 'cause they
didn't bring enough hot girls ?

345
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,960
And that mayor is no outlier.

346
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:41,440
Hungary has been responsible for some
of the ugliest mistreatment of refugees.

347
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:46,480
Disturbing video appears to show
migrants at the main refugee camp

348
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:51,000
being fed like a herd of caged
animals in a holding pen.

349
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,520
It's a shocking video

350
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:55,360
that has garnered attention
from around the world.

351
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:58,440
As waves of desperate migrants
sprint from a holding camp

352
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:01,880
in Hungary, a camerawoman appears
to trip a man

353
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,880
running with his child
in his arms.

354
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:06,520
The woman also kicks other
migrants as they run,

355
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:08,280
including a young girl.

356
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:11,040
Now, the camerawoman
is out of a job.

357
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:13,720
I'm sorry.
She lost her job ?

358
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:15,240
That's absolutely terrible.

359
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:19,480
I'm sure she can find a new one
on ActualMonster.com.

360
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,800
To be fair, she later
apologized, saying

361
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:26,320
"I'm not a heartless, racist,
children-kicking camerawoman".

362
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:28,280
Which I can only presume means

363
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:31,240
she's a loving, accepting,
children-kicking camerawoman,

364
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:35,360
because the children-kicking part
is not really up for debate anymore.

365
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:39,280
And even those countries who
are offering to take refugees

366
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:43,640
are sometimes making those offers
in the most insultingly selective way.

367
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:48,280
Slovakians are saying that they're only
gonna give asylum to Christians.

368
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:52,800
They don't want Muslim migrants
coming into the country,

369
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:55,680
not least because they
haven't got any mosques.

370
00:20:56,560 --> 00:21:00,680
Slovakia, you can't take Muslims in
because you don't have any mosques ?

371
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:03,320
You do know
you can build those, right ?

372
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:06,040
Mosques don't naturally
occur in the wild

373
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:10,400
due to erosion
or particularly devout beavers.

374
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:14,720
Muslims can live anywhere

375
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,160
that other humans can live.

376
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:21,200
Muslims are not like dolphins trying
to resettle in Scottsdale, Arizona.

377
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:25,880
And when refugees are not being
excluded on the basis of religion,

378
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:28,240
they're being accused
of being lazy freeloaders.

379
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:31,680
Just listen to one Polish MEP address
the European Parliament.

380
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:35,560
If we abolished all benefits,

381
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:39,000
then people who don't want to work
and want to live from benefits

382
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:41,400
wouldn't come to Poland
and the rest of Europe.

383
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:43,560
People who want
to work are precious,

384
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,080
however, they are sent back,

385
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:47,720
and we accept only those
who don't want to work.

386
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:51,480
It's a ridiculous policy,
leading to invasion of human trash.

387
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,600
Let us be clear. Human trash.

388
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:56,120
Human garbage that doesn't
want to work.

389
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:59,760
"Human garbage" ? Those
are some pretty strong words

390
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:02,440
coming from the Polish Six-Flags guy.

391
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:06,600
And what he said is not just offensive,
it's also wrong.

392
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:09,880
Research has shown
that while there is some small cost

393
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:13,440
in the short term, eventually
"an influx of lower-wage immigrants"

394
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:17,000
"into a community tends to raise
wages for everyone else".

395
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:20,360
And a working paper
published last year found that

396
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:22,840
"immigration benefited local
populations"

397
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:26,640
"in 19 of the 20 industrialized
countries they studied".

398
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:31,800
Adding immigrants makes things
better 19 times out of 20.

399
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:35,800
That's a success rate matched only
by bacon and Paul Rudd.

400
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:39,240
And incidentally,
it's just a little hard

401
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:42,720
to hear these migrants
and refugees being called lazy

402
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:46,760
considering how hard many of them
have worked to reach Europe.

403
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:49,040
You really wanna talk
about lazy migrants ?

404
00:22:49,120 --> 00:22:50,720
I'm a lazy migrant !

405
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:53,000
I left a country by airplane

406
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:55,480
and the only things
I was escaping were fog,

407
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:58,120
public indifference
and an almost certain future

408
00:22:58,200 --> 00:23:00,560
as the Turtle
of Prince Harry's entourage.

409
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:04,560
I didn't want
to be Royal Turtle !

410
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:11,120
And the maddening thing here is
Europe doesn't even need to do this

411
00:23:11,280 --> 00:23:13,920
for good reasons.
It can do it for selfish ones.

412
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:17,560
Because as a continent,
it is in dire need of new citizens.

413
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:18,680
According to the UN,

414
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:22,000
the average woman needs
to have 2.1 children

415
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:25,240
to maintain the population
of a developed country.

416
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:29,400
But in the European Union,
every single country is below

417
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:30,880
that 2.1 level.

418
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:34,920
By 2050, some countries like
Greece, Portugal and Germany

419
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:40,200
will see their populations drop
by double-digit percentages.

420
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:44,320
That's true. If Europe doesn't open
its doors to more migrants,

421
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:47,600
this is not the changing face
of Europe they should be frightened of.

422
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:50,200
This is !
This one right here !

423
00:23:50,280 --> 00:23:55,160
Not every single asylum seeker is going
to be the perfect economic wellspring.

424
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:58,320
But instead of worrying about
the hypothetical downside

425
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:01,480
of letting these migrants in,
countries should be more worried about

426
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:04,160
the actual downside
of turning them away,

427
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:08,520
if for no other reason that you might
miss out on someone like Noujain,

428
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:12,280
who seems like she would improve
any country that would have her.

429
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:15,000
Just listen to how
she taught herself English.

430
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:17,200
How did you learn
to speak English ?

431
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:20,000
At home with my favorite TV show.

432
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:23,720
- What's that ?
- "Days of Our Lives".

433
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:28,840
With the Sami and EJ struggle.
Yeah, I love them both.

434
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:32,480
How can you not want
this girl in your country ?

435
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:36,080
She loves
"Days of Our Lives" !

436
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,280
She loves "Days of Our Lives,"

437
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:41,520
and specifically,
she loves EJ and Sami.

438
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,840
In fact, even after
weeks of total hell,

439
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:46,240
mortal danger
and inhumane treatment,

440
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:50,400
Noujain's biggest complaint
is that the show killed off EJ,

441
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:51,960
her favorite character.

442
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:53,560
She's right to be upset.

443
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:56,240
EJ and Sami
were magic together.

444
00:24:56,520 --> 00:25:00,720
Yes, you could argue EJ basically
blackmailed Sami into marriage,

445
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,200
then impregnated her,

446
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:05,720
and then worked for Sami's
archnemesis, Nicole Walker,

447
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:07,760
who he then also impregnated.

448
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:10,840
Then he kidnapped Sami's baby
and made her think it was dead,

449
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:13,240
so Sami shot him in the head.

450
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:15,640
That's the kind of thing
couples do.

451
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:18,440
And besides,
they got through all that.

452
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:22,000
And yes, EJ did then cheat
on Sami before their wedding

453
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:24,640
with that trollop
Abigail Deveraux,

454
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:28,360
but he still didn't deserve to die
from yet another gunshot wound.

455
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:31,880
Even though it was reckless for him
to have a secret meeting

456
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:35,920
with hillbilly drug lord Clyde Weston
in the middle of the fucking woods !

457
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:39,080
You idiot, EJ !
How could you die ?

458
00:25:39,160 --> 00:25:44,520
You and Sami were so close
to eternal happiness ! Why, EJ ?

459
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:48,520
My point is...

460
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:53,480
My point is Noujain
has been through enough

461
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:56,720
and any country would
be lucky to have her.

462
00:25:56,800 --> 00:26:00,040
And I know lots of people still have
fears

463
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:02,520
that migrants will
bankrupt social systems,

464
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:04,920
which many studies show
does not happen,

465
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:08,200
fears that migrants might have
an ISIS member lurking among them,

466
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:10,680
which there has been
no credible example of.

467
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:12,440
No one is saying this is easy,

468
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:15,480
but the fact it's so hard
is not a reason to do less,

469
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:17,280
it's a reason to do more,

470
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:20,400
from countries expediting
their application process

471
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:23,320
to properly funding the UN High
Commission for Refugees,

472
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:26,200
whose fund for responding
to Syrian refugees

473
00:26:26,280 --> 00:26:28,760
is less than half
of where it needs to be,

474
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:31,200
to simply, and I know
this sounds crazy,

475
00:26:31,280 --> 00:26:34,520
just not kicking them
when they're moving around !

476
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:39,720
It's a crazy idea !
Just rein your leg in.

477
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:42,640
And there is
actually one final thing

